<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-913-896  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 913 896.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  August 28 1989 v3 n35 p22(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>House may seek lease plan revival.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smithmidford, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Congress may try to implement a plan that was rejected last yearto combine leases on federal computer equipment in order to obtaindiscount financing.andP;  Under the plan the General ServicesAdministration (GSA) would combine all federal leases and privateinvestors would buy shares in the fund to which agencies would paylease fees.andP;  A similar fund was rejected in 1988 because ofworries that individual agencies would conceal procurement costsby deferring them to future budgets.andP;  The new proposal will havesafeguards against such concealment by combining lease paymentsinto a single appropriation year.andP;  The GSA feels that significantsavings can be realized by aggregating capital leases onequipment.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. General Services AdministrationUnited States. CongressPurchasesCost ReductionLeasing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>